<p>
	The two central areas of mechanics are called
	<strong>kinematics</strong> and <strong>dynamics</strong>.
	Each of these can be analyzed <strong>qualitatively</strong> or <strong>quantitatively</strong>
</p>

<p class = 'definition'>
	When studying <strong>kinematics</strong>
	you analyze <emph>how</emph> an object moves
	without analyzing <emph>why</emph> it is moving that way.
	The main concepts in <strong>kinematics</strong> are position, velocity, and acceleration,
	which describe the motion of an object.
</p>

<p class = 'definition'>
	When studying <strong>dynamics</strong>,
	you explain <emph>why</emph> an object moves the
	way that it does.
	The main concept in <strong>dynamics</strong>
	are the forces acting on a particular object, which determine its motion.
</p>


